  "title": "Graphical Interpretations of Algebraic Skills with Functions.",
  "body": " Graphical Interpretations of Algebraic Skills with Functions    To evaluate a function at some value , move to the position on the horizontal axis and then find the vertical coordinate on the graph above or below that point.    To solve an equation of the form , find the -coordinates of all points on the graph whose -coordinate is .    To solve an equation of the form , we are asking for the input values such that and give the same output. Hence we must find the -coordinates of all points of intersection between the graphs of and .    The domain of a function is the set of -coordinates of all points on the graph. This may be visualized as the set of values on the horizontal axis that lie above or below the graph of the function.    The range of a function is the set of -coordinates of all points on the graph. This may be visualized as the set of values on the vertical axis that lie to the left or right of the graph of the function.    "
